<HL>
   LPL Agrees to Be Acquired
</HL>
<DATE>
04/06/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8
</SO>
<CO>
   LPLI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   WILLINGFORD, Conn. -- LPL Technologies Inc. said it agreed
to be acquired by a management group led by Chairman Lawrence
J. DeGeorge and his son Lawrence F. DeGeorge.
   The group will pay $25 a share, $1 a share more than its
previous bid, for the 20% of LPL's approximately 7.5 million
voting shares that are publicly traded. That portion of the
transaction will have a value of $37.5 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said certain affiliated and institutional
holders of LPL shares, including certain members of
management, have agreed to receive $17 in cash and a share of
12% cumulative redeemable preferred stock with a stated value
of $8 for each LPL share.
   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, LPL shares
jumped $1.375 to close at $24.125.
</TEXT>
